Key Match Events: The LA Clippers picked up their fourth-straight win, defeating the Toronto Raptors at Intuit Dome.
The Clippers led by as many as 14 points before Toronto went on a run in the final minutes of the fourth quarter.
Controversial calls by the officiating crew contributed to the game being close down the stretch.
A kick ball violation on Clippers center Ivica Zubac was incorrectly ruled and could not be challenged.
A missed lane violation on Jakob Poeltl’s intentionally missed free throw in the final seconds of the game was another big officiating error.
